-- On release of Burning Crusade (2.0.1), Apexis Guardian roamed freely.
-- 
-- In 2.1.0, when Blizzard added quests and faction rep for Ogri'la, the Apexis Guardian became the objective of  Guardian of the Monument, summoned via the so-called "Simon game". (revised again in 3.3.0)
-- 
-- In 2.2.0, when the (then) new JC recipes were added to the drop table, Apexis Guardian and the Apexis Shard summoned dragons in Blade's Edge Mountains (i.e., Rivendark, Furywing, Insidion, Obsidia) were the only mobs to drop those recipes. See:
-- Design: Rigid Azure Moonstone
-- Design: Shifting Shadow Draenite
-- Design: Shifting Shadow Draenite
-- Design: Veiled Shadow Draenite
-- Design: Deadly Flame Spessarite
-- To complete the quest, simply failing the so-called "Simon game" by paying the 35 Apexis Shard and not even playing will be enough to summon an Apexis Guardian.

-- Apexis Guardians roamed freely prior to patch 2.1
